Two police officers from Parkview Police Station have allegedly been shot and wounded during a hijacking in Emmarentia. According to Northcliff Melville Times, six suspects hijacked a white Audi before being confronted by police, where a shootout ensued. The suspects armed with rifles managed to escape. It is believed that the Audi was then discovered dumped and a second vehicle hijacked. Reports state that one officer was shot in the thigh and the other in the arm. Both were transported to the hospital. Johannesburg metro police are at the scene. -TNA Reporter 